Field Detail

SESSION_TIMER

public static final int SESSION_TIMER
A session is stopped using CoreSessionImp.activityStopSession(Context). After this amount of time (in seconds) then the session will expire.

See Also:
Constant Field Values
Method Detail

getInstance

public static PwCoreSession getInstance()
Return an instance of PwCoreSession. This will provide a handle to be able to start and stop sessions.

Returns:
A Core session instance.
See Also:
CoreSessionImp.activityStartSession(android.content.Context), CoreSessionImp.activityStopSession(android.content.Context)

killSession

public static void killSession()
This will completely wipe out all session related data as well as keys. If this is called, CoreSessionImp.registerKeys(android.content.Context, String, String, String) must be called again to start a new session.

activityStartSession

public void activityStartSession(android.content.Context context)
Start or persist session. Call this on every Activity onStart() method. If a session doesn't exist then a new session will be created. If a session was recently stopped using CoreSessionImp.activityStopSession(Context) then it can be resumed by calling this method before the session expires.

The passed in Context can be the Application context or the Activity context.

RuntimeException will be thrown if CoreSessionImp.registerKeys(Context, String, String, String) was not called First in Application.onCreate()

Parameters:
context - The current context. It can be the Application context or the Activity context.
See Also:
CoreSessionImp.SESSION_TIMER

activityStopSession

public void activityStopSession(android.content.Context context)
Stop session. Call this on every Activity onStop() The session will be stopped but it can be resumed by calling CoreSessionImp.activityStartSession(Context) before the session expires.

The passed in Context can be the Application context or the Activity context.

RuntimeException will be thrown if CoreSessionImp.registerKeys(Context, String, String, String) was not called First in Application.onCreate()

Parameters:
context - The current context. It can be the Application context or the Activity context.
See Also:
CoreSessionImp.SESSION_TIMER

isSessionStarted

public boolean isSessionStarted()
Check if the session has been started or not.

Returns:
True if the session is started and running, false if not started or paused.

registerKeys

public final void registerKeys(android.content.Context context,
                               java.lang.String accessKey,
                               java.lang.String signatureKey,
                               java.lang.String encryptionKey)
Call this before making any additional calls to CoreSessionImp. This must be called in Application.onCreate(). This performs initializations and setup that is required by other method calls.
